.TH ENV 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
env \- print environment variables
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B env
.RI [ prefix ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B env
prints all environment variables, one per line, in
.IR KEY=VALUE
format.
If an optional
.I prefix
is supplied, only variables whose names begin with that prefix are printed.
This is the JLC equivalent of
.BR printenv (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always exits 0.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Print all environment variables:
.B env
.TP
Print only variables starting with \fBXDG_\fR:
.EX
env XDG_
.EE
.TP
Check PATH:
.EX
env PATH
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printenv (1),
.BR export (1p)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
